       <div type="translation" resp="part:kuch">
          <p n="1-6"><supplied reason="subaudible">Vā</supplied> Bhavaśānti <supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> Ku Taptep <supplied reason="subaudible">together with</supplied> a child, Vā Samudra <supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> Ku Dhan <supplied reason="subaudible">together with</supplied> a child, Vā Hitāṅkara <supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> Ku Saṁqap <supplied reason="subaudible">together with</supplied> a child, Ku Saṁtoy, Ku Kañcop. They <supplied reason="subaudible">are the people</supplied> which are given to the shrine. Those who harm <supplied reason="subaudible">them</supplied> will fall in the hell of Avīci <supplied reason="subaudible">with their</supplied> mothers and fathers to the seventh generation.</p>
 	  </div>
       <div type="commentary">
          <p>There are traces of letters before line 1 and after line 6.</p>
          <p>There is a floral decoration on the top of the stela and a line of circles above and below the text.</p>
          <p>Philip Jenner (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Jenner2009_02"/><citedRange unit="page">263</citedRange></bibl>) translates the lines 4-6 as follows: "Persons who harm <supplied reason="subaudible">them</supplied>, they <supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> their fathers and mothers to the seventh generation, - the Avīci hell is the place into which <supplied reason="subaudible">they</supplied> shall fall".</p>
       </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
          <p>Edited by George Cœdès (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Coedes1937-1966_01"/><citedRange unit="volume">6</citedRange><citedRange unit="page">46</citedRange></bibl>) without translation.</p>
